package.name: sfFilebasePlugin
package.summary: Plugin for easily managing filesystem related operations based on SPL.
package.description: Plugin for easily managing filesystem related operations based on SPL.
package.notes: This is the first stable release of sfFilebasePlugin. With space for improvments.

release.notes: * Fixed error in package.xml
* Changed pear channel uri for sfImageTransformPlugin
* Fixed a small bug in sf_filebase_file template which forced the swfupload javascripts to be loaded twice.
* Checked for symfony 1.4 compliency - seems to work so far.

* Improved file upload handling * Added reference to concrete filebase instance to * sfFilebasePluginValidatorFile * sfFilebasePluginUploadedFilesManager * sfFIlebasePluginUploadedFile To avoid weired path errors when using more than one filebase instance in a project. You now don't have to set the filebase path anymore, that will be done automatically as each instance of the widget, helpers and validators retrieve a pointer to the current filebase or the upload manager.
* Removed old GFX-Classes from core_compile.yml * Fixed a bug in saveAs Method the pointed to the wrong image reference
* improve doctrine file behaviour
* improve automatic package install by defining required dependencies
* First stable 1.0 release * More unit tests, coverage of appr. 70 % core functionalities, more 2 come. * Few bugfixes, more improvemenets in utility classes
* Replaced thumbnail and image manipulation capabilities by methods provided by sfImageTransformPlugin. * Started writing unit tests for filebase core functionalities * Various bugfixes
* Fixed a bug in path detection
* Fixed a bug in an throwed exception (missing sprintf)
* Fixed a bug in parsing windows paths
* Fixed bug that prevented the ext tree from beeing rendered in internet explorer
* Added usablity improvements in gallery view: * Edit and delete button for folders * Edit and delete button for files * Direct download by click on image thumbnail
* Added usablity improvements in gallery view, icon to edit folder data and a few more little things

* Fixed bug that nested sets tree was not updated when an item was deleted by admin generated modules. * Improved mime type detection by recursive dependancy list, todo: maintain this list or steal one ;)
* Cleaned up CSS in admin modules
* Added synch mechanism between multi file upload and ext tree.
* Added SWFUpload support based on sfWidgetFormInputSWFUploadPlugin * Added Tree editing support through sfWidgetFormTreePlugin
* Fixed a bug that prevents sfFilebasePluginUploadedFile from extending sfValidatedFile when sfFilebasePluginValidatorFile was not previously included.
* Fixed a bug in sfFilebaseTask * tasks preventing accessing sfContext in a multi application environment.
* Added tag cloud support to admin area

* Fixed **various** bugs in core filebase. So: * Directories and files can now be moved correctly be analyzing move/copy destination * chmod on directory now returns instance of sfFilebaseDirectory * Uploaded files are now saved under the correct filename given * minor improvements * files can now be stored under varous file names with spaces and special chars * PluginsfAbstractFile not longer declared abstract, this behaviour throws an exception in the symfony model generator. * Tags are now stored in the same relation for more easy filtering. * So schema.yml and tag model classes are removed by this release.
* Added overview page to admin area * Fixed bug in thumbnail generation when both width & height are set * Added main.css to package for demonstration purposes

* Added core_compile.yml to add the core libraries to cache. * Added tasks form maintanance. * Fixed sfFilebasePlugin::copyFile() and added improved file type recognition * Fixed sfFilebasePlugin::copyDirectory() and added improved file type recognition * Removed old sample files * Worked on install instructions for admin area * Did some minor bugfixes and improvements.
* Admin area improved: Thumbnail images and download links in admin generated forms.
* Admin area improved * Bug fix in filemanager * Switched to doctrine ORM * Small api improvements to sfFilebasePlugin * Can now copy and move directories recursively
* Admin area improved * Switched to doctrine ORM * Small api improvements to sfFilebasePlugin * Can now copy and move directories recursively
* Fixed indentation problem in schema.yml * Added filemanager module * Improved validation * sfFilebasePluginFileValidator now works with admin generator
* Added filemanager module * Improved validation * sfFilebasePluginFileValidator now works with admin generator
* Added preserveTransparency for images created by GD adapter
* Improved mime type detection * sfFilebasePluginValidatorFile: added isEmpty() methods and changed mime detections to proxies for sfFilebasePluginUtil::getMimeType()
* Worked on sfFilebasePluginValidatorFile
* Worked on sfFilebasePluginValidatorFile
* Worked on documentation
* Fixed files in package.xml
* New files are now included in package.xml

* Improved directory deletion: sfFilebasePluginDirectory::delete() now gets a parameter, that, if set to TRUE, deletes the directory and its contents, recursively by internally calling sfFilebasePluginDirectory::deleteRecursive()

* Fixed bug in helper -.- * V 0.5.1: * Worked on improved symfony integration:
* Implemented factory method sfFilebasePlugin::getInstance(); * Implemented sfFilebasePluginWebRequest, refer to README to learn about how to use this class in factories.yml * You now can specify the default filebase- and cache directory in your apps/yourapp/config/app.yml. Refer to the README file or look at the phpdoc of sfFilebasePlugin * Added helper sfFilebasePluginHelper get_filebase(): retrieves your filebase in a view

* Worked on improved symfony integration:
* Implemented factory method sfFilebasePlugin::getInstance(); * Implemented sfFilebasePluginWebRequest, refer to README to learn about how to use this class in factories.yml * You now can specify the default filebase- and cache directory in your apps/yourapp/config/app.yml. Refer to the README file or look at the phpdoc of sfFilebasePlugin * Added helper sfFilebasePluginHelper get_filebase(): retrieves your filebase in a view
* Added sfFilebasePluginValidatorFile for native File upload validation.
* Added link to sample project to README
* Added link to sample project to README

* Minor improvements * add getFileExists to sfFilebasePlugin, modified sfFilebasePluginFile::fileExists() as a proxy * add isLink() * add unsupported Exception when Link is requested by sfFilebasePlugin::getFilebaseFile() * Double slashes removed in sfFilebasePlugin::getFilebaseFile()
* Worked on README, installation notes and a few syntax improvements
* Finally removed optional deps from packege.xml to get things work.
* Changed release and api state to stable for installer. hope it works.
* Trying to fill in this package.xml properly :'(
* Fixed bug while retrieving thumbnail representation
* Fixed README * Fixed bug while retrieving thumbnail representation
